sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as OpenShift Gateway<br/>(Envoy)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant KRBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Predictor as Predictor Container<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant S3 as S3/GCS/Azure Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Controller as kserve-controller-manager
    participant StorageInit as storage-initializer<br/>(Init Container)
    participant Scheduler as llm-d-inference-scheduler<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Workers as Prefill/Decode Workers<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Note over Client, S3: Flow 1: InferenceService with Auth (RawDeployment mode)
    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/{model}:predict<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>KRBAC: Forward request<br/>HTTPS TLS (serving cert)<br/>Port 8443/TCP
    KRBAC->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    K8sAPI-->>KRBAC: Allow/Deny
    KRBAC->>Predictor: Proxy to app<br/>HTTP plaintext (pod-internal)<br/>Port 8080/TCP
    Predictor-->>KRBAC: Prediction Response
    KRBAC-->>Gateway: Response (TLS)
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response (HTTPS)

    Note over Client, Predictor: Flow 2: InferenceService without Auth
    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/{model}:predict<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>Predictor: Forward request<br/>HTTP plaintext<br/>Port 80/TCP
    Predictor-->>Gateway: Prediction Response
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response (HTTPS)

    Note over Controller, S3: Flow 3: Storage Initializer Model Download
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch/Reconcile CRs<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount token
    Controller->>Controller: Create Pod with init container
    StorageInit->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Cloud provider credentials (Secret)
    S3-->>StorageInit: Model artifacts
    StorageInit->>StorageInit: Write to shared volume

    Note over Client, Workers: Flow 4: LLMInferenceService with Disaggregated Serving
    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>Scheduler: Route via InferencePool<br/>HTTP plaintext<br/>Port 8080/TCP
    Scheduler->>Workers: Schedule to prefill worker<br/>HTTP plaintext<br/>Port 8080/TCP
    Workers->>Workers: Prefill → KV cache → Decode
    Workers-->>Scheduler: Streaming response
    Scheduler-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>Client: Streaming JSON (HTTPS)
